The transcriptional coactivator Eya1 exerts transcriptional repressive activity by interacting with REST corepressors and DNA recognition sequences to maintain nephron progenitor identity¶

EYA Transcriptional Coactivator And Phosphatase 1 (Eya1) plays an important role in maintaining nephron progenitor cells (NPCs) but it has no intrinsic DNA-binding activity. Some reasch reported that EYA1 protein interact with SIX2 protein to regulate gene expression and cell proliferation that is critical for controling NPCs Maintenance. However, the machanism of the Eya1 network to mediate cell proliferation and maintain the NPCs identity is poorly understood.

In order to identify genes which are associated with Eya1 in NPCs, the researchers performed RNA-seq experiments. First. they use FACS to isolate tdTomato+ cells from control (Eya1CreER/+;tdTomato) and Eya1cKO (Eya1CreER/+;Eya1fl/fl;R26-Tdtomato) kidneys of mice embryo at E12.5∼E12.75. Second, mRNA was purified from total RNA using magnetic beads. Third, RNA-seq libraries were prepared and sequenced using Illumina NextSeq 500 with single-end 75-bp. Lastly, mapping reads to mouse genome mm10 and analysze differencial expression and functional annotation.

GEO data source https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE202956

Reference adapt from: Cellular and Molecular Mechanisms of Kidney Development: From the Embryo to the Kidney Organoid. Niloofar Khoshdel Rad,Nasser Aghdami, and Reza Moghadasali. Front Cell Dev Biol. 2020; 8: 183. doi: 10.3389/fcell.2020.00183\ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7105577/

blue line means median,\ yellow box: 25-75%,\ quality -> higher than 20 -> good

no sequence with low quality => all of sequence have high avarage quality score

Theoretically, distribution of the four bases doesn't change with base position. However, the line is wobbing, it has a biased position. \ The reason is random hexamers (certain hexamers) are favoured during the priming step of library production.\ This index failed doesn't affect the result.

GC content across all the sequences, should be normal distribution and close to the theoretical distribution.\ The result is good.\ *If not match with blue line -> having specific contaminants in the library

show uncalled bases in the library

Show the library is all the same length or not.

Show how unique the sequences are within the library. Sequence duplicate level 1 means sequence occurs once. \ The index failed (or say RNAseq almost always "fail") caused by highly expressed genes which are flagged as duplicates.\ Therefore, we don't need to worry about this fail.

Sequences with low duplication levels (2-9 copies) => ‘normal’ genes \Sequences with moderate duplication (10 – 100 copies) => rRNA or some repeat sequences.

Look for individual sequence which are over represented (>0.1% of the total sequence) within the set.\ Possible Source: contaminants (primer or adaptor used in the various sequencing platforms)\ In the QC result, we don't have the overrepresented sequences (good).

This index is good.
